<CONTENT id="_3793147_1"><TITLE value="Session 7"/><TITLECOLOR value="#000000"/><DESCRIPTION
   value=""/><BODY><TEXT>&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 10pt;"&gt;image from &lt;a href="https://www.researchgate.net/figure/Structural-Levels-of-the-Personal-Data-Security-System-PDSS_fig1_307570457" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;https://www.researchgate.net/figure/Structural-Levels-of-the-Personal-Data-Security-System-PDSS_fig1_307570457&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav/xid-46884695_1" alt="" width="460" height="267" style="border: 0px solid #000000;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 14pt;"&gt;Introduction&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;During this session we will examine methods used to protect an organisation's data&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h5&gt;News&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://ia.acs.org.au/content/ia/article/2024/asic-takes-down-3-500-scam-websites-in-six-months.html?ref=newsletter&amp;amp;deliveryName=DM20857" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;ASIC takes down 3,500 scam websites in six months | Information Age | ACS&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.indusface.com/blog/cve-2024-1071-ultimate-member-wordpress-plugin/?utm_campaign=newsletter-march-2024&amp;amp;utm_medium=email&amp;amp;_hsmi=296861614&amp;amp;utm_source=email-newsletter" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Ultimate Member WordPress Plugin (CVE-2024-1071) | Indusface Blog&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Here’s how a&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt; JavaScript Supply Chain Attack&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; works:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Step 1: A 3&lt;sup&gt;rd&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;nbsp;party JavaScript library is compromised&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Step 2: Customer visits the webpage like the payment page with the compromised JS file&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Step 3: Data is exfiltrated one record (credit card number for example) at a time&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;100K websites were compromised using this tactic with the &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;pollyfill.io JS hack&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; last month (July 2024).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;p id="anonymous_element_24"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 14pt;"&gt;Topic&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;We will investigate common infrastructure, equipment, and and software that is employed to protect the organisation from cyber security attacks.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 14pt;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Out of Session Activity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;Review protecting personal data.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 14pt;"&gt;Portfolio Tasks&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 10pt;"&gt;Check assessments tab.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Complete outstanding work&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;</TEXT><TYPE
